    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Floor coverings handwoven in or around the city of Kayseri in central Turkey. The best-known rugs from this district are those produced in the 20th century, largely for sale to tourists and undiscriminating collectors.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
